b'' b'' b'wgt is the wordup graphics toolkit, designed by yours truly and my' b'co-programmer (and brother) chris egerter. it is a turbo/borland c++ graphics' b'library for programming in vga. we are currently producing it as' b'shareware, but in a few years it may be a commercial product (excuse typos,' b"there's no backspace on this terminal). features include:" b'' b'- loading and saving bit-images (called blocks from herein)' b'- flipping, resizing and warping blocks' b'- loading and saving palette, fading, several in memory at once' b'- graphics primitives such as line, circle, bar, rectangle' b'- region fill (not the usually useless floodfill)' b'- sprites (animated bitmaps), up to onscreen at once' b'- joystick/mouse support' b'- sb support (voc and cmf)' b'- tile-based game creation using pixel tiles to create' b"a tile map (or game world) like in duke nuke 'em" b'- number of sprites increased to b'- professional sprite creator utility and map maker' b'- routines to simplify scrolling games using maps, etc' b'- fli playing routines, sprites can be animated over the fli while playing' b'- pcx support, soon gif' b'- ems/xms coming soon as well' b'' b'' b'files available on: (use mget wgt*.zip)' b'' b'simtel20 and mirrors pd1:<msdos.turbo-c' b'' b'nic.funet.fi pub/msdos/games/programming' b'' b'some sites may not have recent files, contact me for info regarding the up-to-' b'date information.' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' 